{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Fire Pig|kanji=丁亥|romaji=hinoto i|onyomi=teigai|p=dīhài|w=ting-hai|mi=tʰiŋ⁵³ xaɪ̯|y=deng1 hoi6|j=deng1 hoi6|ci=tɛŋ hɐi|mc=tæŋ ɣəi|oc-bs=tæŋ ɢəʔ}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Fire Pig also known as 丁亥''' (hinotoi, teika no inoshishi, teigai) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft}}.

It is the 24th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Besshi|ja|丙戌|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Jinshi|ja|戊子|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Pig|ja|亥|1=Pig (zodiac)|lt=Pig (亥)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水|12=draft|12=draft}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|12=draft|12=draft}}) (i.e. Water overcomes Fire).

== 丁亥の年 ==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦|12=draft|12=draft}} that leaves a remainder of 27 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年|12=draft|12=draft}} of {{ill|Teigai|ja|丁亥|12=draft|12=draft}}.
