'''Yin Fire Pig also known as 丁亥''' (hinotoi, teika no inoshishi, teigai) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

It is the 24th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Besshi|ja|丙戌|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Jinshi|ja|戊子|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft}} symbol {{ill|Pig|ja|亥|1=Pig (zodiac)|lt=Pig (亥)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) (i.e. Water overcomes Fire).

